{{Unreferenced|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox power station |name = Trillo Nuclear Power Plant |image = <!--(filename only)--> |image_caption = |location_map = Spain |country = Spain |location = | coordinates = {{coord|40|42|4|N|2|37|19|W|type:landmark_region:ES_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[Iberdrola]] (48%) |operator = [[CNAT]] |construction_began = |commissioned = 1988 |decommissioned = |np_reactor_supplier = |np_reactor_type = PWR |ps_units_operational = 1 × 1003 MW |ps_units_decommissioned = |ps_units_uc = |ps_units_planned = |ps_electrical_capacity = <!--(MW)--> |ps_annual_generation = <!--(GW·h. Needs 'for_year' to be set.)--> |status = O |cost = |website = }} '''Trillo Nuclear Power Plant''' is a [[nuclear power station]] in [[Spain]].
It consists of one [[pressurized water reactor]] (PWR) of 1066&nbsp;MWe. Construction of unit one began in 1979, and first criticality was on 14&nbsp;May 1988.
A planned second identical unit was cancelled soon after construction began following a change of government in 1983.{{cn|date=August 2016}}
