{{EngvarB|date=July 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox EU legislation |type=Directive |title= Waste Framework Directive |number= 2008/98/EC |madeby=[[European Parliament]] & [[European Council|Council]] |madeunder= Article 175(1) |OJref= |OJrefurl= http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2008:312:0003:0030:EN:PDF |made= 19 November 2008 |commenced= 12 December 2008 |implementation= |CommProp= |ESCOpin= |ParlOpin= |Reports= |replaces= 75/439/EEC, 91/689/EEC and 2006/12/EC |amends= |amendedby= |replacedby= |status=Current }}
The '''Waste Framework Directive (WFD)''' is a [[European Union]] [[Regulation (European Union)|Directive]] of 17 June 2008.<ref>Directive [2008/98/EC] of the European Parliament and of the Council on waste.</ref> The first Waste Framework Directive dates back to 1975<ref>(Directive 75/442/EEC)</ref> and was substantially amended in 1991.<ref>(91/156/EEC)</ref>
The aim of the WFD was to lay the basis to turn the EU into a recycling society.
One of the features of the WFD is the [[European Waste Hierarchy]].
